page.title: 02DWELLINGS
page.content: { { { { { }The homes in Harbury range from very old to very new. There are bungalows, detached and semi-detached houses, flats for families and senior citizens. New housing estates are Manor Orchard, Sutcliffe Pastures, Temple End, Butt Lane, Queen's Close, Binswood End,Constance Drive, The Pound. There are council estates at Pineham Avenue, Bush Heath Lane, Manor Orchard, Leycester Close, The Pound, Crown Close and Vicarage Lane. New buildings are mainly of brick and old buildings of stone and timber. The roofs are mainly of slate and tiles. Two houses have thatched roofs. Most types of doors and windows are to be found.
